\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
Just two up and two down. Well there'd be a scullery at the back, which was used as a wash house, and then a kitchen and I think there was a small sitting room, and two bedrooms. Which }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12718837\charrsid15301266 mean
\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266  we had to get out as we got bigger - that was the reason for moving. We had three children when we left there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did anyone else besides you and your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did your mother have anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did your mother or father make or mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Oh mother did. Mother was clothes mender and baker. She used to bake her own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 You would I suppose buy some clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 And these would be bought new or second-hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 All new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Where were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 At the Co-op.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 How often would you say that you had new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 We had a new suit every sermons. Every Sunday School sermons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 And what about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
We'd have a new pair of shoes. We used to be fit out every May when it was Sunday School sermons. We'd have new clothes and shoes and those would go on for twelve months and then you would take them for school, for everyday wear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did your father ever mend your shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes. On occasions yes. By the way, we wore clogs not shoes. We had a pair of shoes for Sunday, not for everyday of the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did your father help your mother at all with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
Yes. He would help with the washing up at night. He'd mend.... He'd do his own repairs in the house. I wouldn't say he did anything else apart from washing up, helping to wash up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did he make the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Oh yes, on occasions, yes. He would be up early in the morning and have the fire going for us to get up to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did he do any decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Apart from white-washing and lime-washing, no. Well yes, he would do some ordinary plain painting in the hous
e. He'd keep the place going in decent order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did he ever do any cleaning or cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes when mother was confined and in bed with the children. He had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did he do anything for you as children? Like dressing, undressing or feeding you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 In emergencies, yes. But not normally, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Would he read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Would he take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Would he look after you while she went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 As children did you have any tasks that you had to carry out regularly at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
Yes. Saturday mornings you had certain jobs to do. I had to clean the knives and forks, spoons and cutlery. My sisters had their regular jobs on Saturday mornings helping Mum 
to clean the house. The house had to be gone through, cleaned right through. And we all had to do certain jobs that were allocated to us, and we didn't get our pocket money, which was a 1/2d until we'd done them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Was this confined to Saturdays or did you have to do things throughout the week as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
As far as I can remember it was confined to Saturdays. Or possibly maybe Friday night; if there was something important on like a Sunday School outing or something like that we'd do them Friday night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 How long did you go on doing this? After you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
Yes. We always had to do something in the house. I started to earn money when I was. In fact my first recollection of earning money was when I got 2d. a week for carrying breakfasts up into the spinning mill. In those days the spinners started to work at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 6}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. They used to break for breakfast at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}8 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
 till half past. And if they wanted a cooked breakfast it had to be carried into them. If they wanted a cooked breakfast, eggs an
d bacon or bacon and tomatoes. My first job was carrying breakfasts up to 2 spinners in the cotton mill which earned me a penny each from each of them. Then of course when I was going to school I took up papers. Helped the family income earning 2/- a week
 
taking on papers every day. Yes my sister went as a half timer. There was a need as the family grew up for more income. Everything was geared to earning more money, in order to get more clothes, to live better. When we were very young father's age wasn't 
a
n adequate one for 3 children or four children or five or six as it was in later years. By the time the last 2, the 2 younger, I was earning 2 shillings a week on a paper round and my elder sisters would be earning 2 or 3 shillings a week as a half timer 
in the weaving shed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult? Helping to feed or dress them and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did the younger children do anything to help the older ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Can't ever remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Were you expected to go to bed at a particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes. When we were very young we were put to bed at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 7}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, as we grew up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} and later {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
. And of course the light nights in the summer we didn't go to bed until it was dark.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 At what age did you start to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 About eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 And was it your mother who put you to bed before then or did your father do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 One or the other. If we'd been naughty father would put us to bed with a slap, if we'd been good mother would put us to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did you share the bedroom with anybody?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
Yes until we moved we had to. The three children had to sleep in one room. Two boys and a girl. By the time I was eight of course we had moved into a bigger house and the girls shared one bedroom and the two boys shared another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 We used to bath in the old tin bath in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 On Friday nights and the three children had their baths one after the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 How often did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Every week on a Friday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 In the kitchen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Was there any occasions when you would eat in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Where did your mother do the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 That would be on a fire range would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 What time would you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 And would you all have breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Oh he would go off to work at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 6}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} and take his breakfast with him. He'd take sandwiches with him to the foundry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Would he have anything at all before he went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Oh I expect so. He would probably cook himself s
ome bacon. Yes I think he used to get a breakfast. Or probably I should say he would have some porridge, oatmeal porridge, and milk to go off with and may be a cup of tea. And take some bacon sandwiches with him. For the breakfast half hour - 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}eight o'clock{\*\xmlclose} till half pad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 What did the rest of you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
It varied. Bread and butter and maybe when eggs were cheap we'd have an egg between the two of us. Or porridge - we'd just have porridge and nothing else. And Oatmeal porridge Easter day was the one day in the year we had a whole egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Did you ever have anything special on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 We had a joint when times were good enough, permitted, father was in full work. We'd have a big Sunday dinner with beef and }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12718837\charrsid15301266 Yorkshire}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266  pudding, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12718837\charrsid15301266 tomato}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 But you wouldn't have anything special at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Tea and cocoa. Generally cocoa at breakfast in winter time. That was our winter beverage, both for breakfast and supper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Now you said you had a big joint on Sundays for dinner time, what about the other days in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 
We'd have the cold meat on Monday. We'd have stew on Tuesday, or fish, or if there was enough meat left over Mother would make it into cottage pie, or she would stew up the meat and serve it with boiled potatoes. Wednesday was baking day and we had 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Lancashire{\*\xmlclose} potato pie, that was the standard thing. We might have anything on Thursday. Perhaps if the wages permitted it we might have chops - chops were a luxury. But I
 can remember the time when I've gone out, mother used to send me to the butchers when we were really hard up and father was out of work, I'd go out with 2d and buy herbs and we'd just have soup made out of perhaps some bone and what we called pot herbs. 
Q
uite a lot, you'd get an onion and a carrot and a bit of cabbage for about 2d, two-penny worth of pot herbs and a bone from the butchers, which he might give to you if you were a regular customer. And mum would make soup up and put some peas or lentils in
 it and we might have that one day a week.
