\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes. He used to run up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Kay Street{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. There were two big foundries in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Kay Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. I can remember all these chaps coming out with their black faces rushing up to catch special trams which were waiting for them at the top of Kay Street to bring them up to 
Astley Bridge and they would practically run in the house, sit down to a hot meal, just have a pull at the pipe for five minutes and then off back. They were brought back of course. They had an hour's break. But there were no canteen or feeding arrangemen
ts inside the foundry not until the war came. I think there were some canteen meals during the first wo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2233513\charrsid15301266 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 ld wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2233513\charrsid15301266 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266  which was the start of canteen meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13773995 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 So you'd all have your dinner together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11733122 FB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8596504\charrsid15301266 Yes.
